		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>Sept 16<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1862</date></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>31 Nassau St.</placeName></p>
				<p><addressee>I. Leeser Esq.</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your letter of yesterday<lb/> is at hand.  Enclosed find &#36;2.62&#44; <hi rend="underline">large</hi><lb/> amount of <persName>Mr Loewe&#39;s</persName> indebtedness.</p>
				<p>When I first wrote you I was under the<lb/> impression that <persName>Mr Loewe</persName> owed you<lb/> a balance&#44; independent of the advertisement<lb/> last inserted.  Your receipted bill being<lb/> only for the latter&#44; of course satisfies me to<lb/> the contrary.  Your commission to <persName>Mr<lb/> Isaacs</persName> with your regards to <persName>Mr Loewe</persName> will<lb/> both be attended to.</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Yours Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Joseph H. Levy</persName>.</p>
